WEBVTT

00:02:59.904 --> 00:03:04.396
DD: Well, it's very nice to be here,
and thanks for the dramatic introduction.

00:03:04.420 --> 00:03:06.087
I'm very glad to hear it.

00:03:07.230 --> 00:03:11.649
CA: So David, in the first
TED Talk you gave, you had this phrase

00:03:11.673 --> 00:03:14.466
that you quoted, really,
from Stephen Hawking.

00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:19.617
Stephen Hawking referred to humans
as basically "chemical scum"

00:03:19.641 --> 00:03:22.442
on the surface of an obscure planet.

00:03:22.466 --> 00:03:28.117
And that's actually quite a common view
of how science is thought of

00:03:28.141 --> 00:03:29.522
as treating humans, you know.

00:03:29.546 --> 00:03:32.022
We started thinking
we were the center of everything,